# Statify Frontend - Cursor IDE Rules

## Project Context
This is a Next.js frontend for a multi-tenant status page system using TypeScript and shadcn/ui.

## Code Style
- TypeScript for all files
- Use functional components with hooks
- Prefer named exports
- Use `@/` path alias for imports

## Framework
- Next.js 14+ with App Router
- Pages in `src/app/`
- Components in `src/components/`

## Styling
- TailwindCSS utility classes
- shadcn/ui for component primitives
- No inline styles

## Component Patterns
```tsx
// Prefer this structure
interface ComponentProps {
  title: string;
  children: React.ReactNode;
}

export function Component({ title, children }: ComponentProps) {
  return (
    <div className="p-4">
      <h1>{title}</h1>
      {children}
    </div>
  );
}
```

## shadcn/ui Usage
- Import from `@/components/ui/`
- Add new components: `npx shadcn-ui@latest add [name]`
- Available: Button, Card, Input, Dialog, etc.

## State Management
- React hooks for local state
- Custom hooks in `src/hooks/`
- No Redux (keep it simple)

## API Calls
- Use fetch or custom API client
- Handle loading and error states
- Type all responses

## File Naming
- Components: PascalCase (`ServiceCard.tsx`)
- Utilities: camelCase (`formatDate.ts`)
- Types: PascalCase (`Service.ts`)

## Best Practices
- Keep components under 200 lines
- Extract logic to custom hooks
- Use TypeScript strictly (no `any`)
- Handle loading and error states
